				\begin{document}$$1 - J(a,b) = 1 - \frac{{\left| {a \cap b} \right|}}{{\left| {a \cup b} \right|}}$$\end{document}1-J(a,b)=1-a∩ba∪bwhere J(a, b) is Jaccard similarity coefficient and is defined as the number of genes in the intersection of a and b divided by the number of genes in the union of a and b. Based on the Jaccard distance, we generated a hierarchical cluster tree to group the gene sets whose distances are less than 0.3.
